Phase 0: Pre-Conditions
These items must be completed BEFORE any Phase 1 code changes begin. They establish the
infrastructure, process, and tooling that all subsequent work depends on.
P0-01: GitHub Actions CI/CD Pipeline
Priority Effort Grade Impact
BLOCKER Medium (4 hours) All Workstreams E→D
Current State
No CI/CD pipeline exists. All deployments are manual. There is no automated enforcement of code
quality, tests, or security checks. A broken deployment can reach production with no safeguard.
Fix / Implementation Required
Commit .github/workflows/ci.yml from the GitHub Package to the repository. The pipeline runs on every
PR and every push to main. It executes: (1) pnpm install, (2) tsc --noEmit, (3) eslint ., (4) pnpm test, (5)
pnpm build, (6) pnpm audit --audit-level=critical. Deployment to Render only triggers when all steps
pass.
Expected Outcome
Every PR and merge to main automatically runs all quality checks. No broken code can be merged. No
deployment happens without all gates passing.
Validation Check
Open a PR with a deliberate TypeScript error (e.g., const x: number = "string"). The CI pipeline must fail
and block the merge.
P0-02: Branch Strategy and PR Template
Priority Effort Grade Impact
BLOCKER Low (1 hour) Process Discipline
Current State

---

No branching strategy is defined. Developers commit directly to main. No PR template exists. Changes
cannot be traced to plan items.
Fix / Implementation Required
In GitHub Settings > Branches: protect main and develop, require PR reviews, require CI to pass before
merging. Commit .github/PULL_REQUEST_TEMPLATE.md from the GitHub Package. Branch naming:
feature/<item-id>-<description> and hotfix/<item-id>-<description>.
Expected Outcome
No developer can push directly to main or develop. Every PR must reference a Grand Master Plan item
ID and include validation output.
Validation Check
Attempt to push directly to main. GitHub must reject with a branch protection error.
P0-03: All Environment Variables Set in Render
Priority Effort Grade Impact
BLOCKER Low (1 hour) Security A, Integrations D→C
Current State
Multiple required environment variables are missing from the Render deployment. Features that depend
on them silently fail with no error message to the user.
Fix / Implementation Required
Log in to Render dashboard. Navigate to the service > Environment. Add every variable listed in
Appendix E. For secrets, generate new values: openssl rand -hex 32. Never commit secrets to the
repository.
Expected Outcome
All features that depend on environment variables work correctly. No silent failures due to missing
configuration.
Validation Check

---

Run python3 scripts/validate.py --check ENV. All 31 environment variables must be present and non-
empty.
P0-04: Database Seed Script
Priority Effort Grade Impact
High Medium (4 hours) Testing D→B
Current State
No seed script exists. Every developer creates their own test data inconsistently. There is no way to test
features end-to-end without manually creating records.
Fix / Implementation Required
Commit scripts/seed.ts from the GitHub Package. Run with: npx tsx scripts/seed.ts. Creates one realistic
record in every active table. Creates test user: email test@cepho.ai, PIN 1234 (bcrypt hashed).
Expected Outcome
Any developer can run the seed script and immediately have a fully populated database. Every feature
can be tested end-to-end.
Validation Check
Run npx tsx scripts/seed.ts on a fresh database. Log in with test@cepho.ai / PIN 1234. Victoria's
Briefing must show a briefing. Tasks must show tasks. Projects must show projects.
P0-05: Architecture Decision Records
Priority Effort Grade Impact
Medium Low (2 hours) Documentation C→B
Current State
No record of why key technical decisions were made. New developers cannot understand the reasoning
behind the architecture.
Fix / Implementation Required

---

Create /docs/decisions/ folder. Write ADR-001 (tRPC), ADR-002 (Supabase), ADR-003 (Drizzle ORM),
ADR-004 (Render), ADR-005 (Vite + React), ADR-006 (TailwindCSS). Each ADR has: Context, Decision,
Alternatives Considered, Consequences.
Expected Outcome
New developers understand why the platform is built the way it is. Technical debates are not repeated.
Validation Check
The /docs/decisions/ folder contains at least 6 ADR files, each with all four required sections.


